search_results.title: Russell Ohl
search_results.snippet: Russell Shoemaker Ohl (January 30, 1898 – March 20, 1987) was an American scientist who is generally recognized for patenting the modern solar cell.

search_results.title: Brian Ohl, Adjunct Professor
search_results.snippet: Brian Ohl is an adjunct professor in the Public Administration and International Affairs Department. He teaches undergraduate and graduate courses.

search_results.title: Jean-Pierre Ohl
search_results.snippet: Jean-Pierre Ohl (born 1959) is a French writer. He was born in Onesse-Laharie, a small village in the Landes forest in Southwest France.
